<p> My robot dog was first created in a browser-based software called TinkerCAD. It provided basic support and I started my project on it because of its user-friendly capabilities. </p>
<p>Here is a public view link:
https://www.tinkercad.com/things/75EoaUac4LI-robot-dog. </p>
<p> It featured servos, a screen, an ultrasonic distance sensor, and a ESP32 camera module. </p>
<p> At the time, coding it was a little hard for me, as I wasn't familiar with using an arduino to code, however, in my opinion, it was a pivotal starting point for me. </p>

